text.tspan: Protestant cancels the play of a card as an
event. Must be played after event is
declared but before it is resolved. Can not
be used to cancel Mandatory Events,
Combat cards, Response cards, or non-
Papal Home cards (Papal Bull and Leipzig
Debate may be canceled). Discard the
event; this player's impulse is over.
Protestant may not initiate debates for
rest of turn. Commit Luther (if not
already); he can not be added into debates
with Here I Stand until next turn.
Protestant, and Luther must be alive.
